## Workflow

1. Read `docs/CONTEXT.md` to understand decisions (especially anything relevant to this task).
2. Read `.ralph-tui/progress.md` for patterns, gotchas, and learnings from earlier iterations.
3. Implement the task following the acceptance criteria above.
4. Run quality gates (see below) — fix any failures before continuing.
5. Commit with message: `feat({{taskId}}): {{taskTitle}}`
6. Update `.ralph-tui/progress.md`: append a `## [{{taskId}}]` section with what you did, files changed, and any patterns/gotchas worth noting. If you discovered a reusable pattern, also add it to the `## Codebase Patterns` section at the top.
7. Signal completion.

## Quality Gates (REQUIRED — all must pass)

```bash
pnpm typecheck      # tsc --noEmit — must pass with zero errors
pnpm lint           # eslint — must pass with zero warnings
pnpm build          # next build — must succeed
```

If a test runner is configured (`pnpm test`), run that too.

## Stop Condition

If the work described is already fully implemented and meets the acceptance criteria, verify the quality gates pass and signal completion immediately — do not re-implement.

